def: One of a sect among the Jews in the time of our Savior,remarkable for their strictness and abstinence.
Strong of wing; strong on the wing. [Poetic] Davies (HolyRoode).

Pleasantry or slight satire; banter; jesting language;satirical merriment.Let raillery be without malice or heat. B. Jonson.Studies employed on low objects; the very naming of them issufficient to turn them into raillery. Addison.
The act of accrediting; as, letters of accreditation.
A forest officer appointed to walk over a certain space forinspection; a forester.
One who inserts in a category or list; one who classifies.Emerson.
A little or insignificant dandy; a contemptible fop.
Calcium tungstate, a mineral of a white or pale yellowish colorand of the tetragonal system of crystallization.
